item.title: Jury selection in Alec Baldwin's "Rust" shooting trial underway
item.description: Jury selection began Tuesday in Alec Baldwin's trial over the death of cinematographer Halyna Hutchins on the "Rust" film set in New Mexico. Baldwin is charged with involuntary manslaughter in connection with the 2021 shooting. CBS News' Elise Preston has the latest on the Monday's pretrial hearing and Tuesday's jury selection.

item.title: Trump VP pick expected soon as he tries to distance himself from Project 2025
item.description: Former President Donald Trump is expected to announce his 2024 running mate soon. Meanwhile, he is trying to distance himself from the Heritage Foundation's "Project 2025" proposal, which has been circulating online as his potential future agenda if he wins the presidential election. CBS News campaign reporter Olivia Rinaldi has more.
